      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CANTARA PEARL (5) chased the lead early from the inside and boxed on well to finish second, beaten 0.8 lengths (18.05) at this track in a Other over 305m. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Expected to feature in the finish again. ESKIMO ROMAN (4) wasn't far away at the finish when 4th and beaten only 3.5 lengths (23.87) at this track. Boasts two wins from five starts out of this box. Has ability and can atone. CADILLAC GIRL (1) showed little early speed at her last couple, the latest finishing fourth (18.20) in a Other at this track. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Can figure in the finish. HENRY BALE (2) is worth a look over a shorter journey this time.",
